00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:24,657
Yeah. There's no guns,
the food is terrific,

495
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:27,494
and there's ample parking.

496
00:21:29,037 --> 00:21:30,538
Could we talk to you
for a minute?

497
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:32,582
Of course.

498
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:34,376
Deal me out.

499
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:40,798
How'd you find this place?

500
00:21:40,882 --> 00:21:42,634
Oh, I've gotten sober here
many times.

501
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:45,053
It's a wonderful program.
The owner's a buddy.

502
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:47,263
- He lets me rent the room.
- Nice.

503
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:48,848
So, what's it cost
to get the cure here?

504
00:21:48,932 --> 00:21:51,059
Last time I got a nudge
from the judge?

505
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:52,894
- About 75 grand a month.
- (scoffs)

506
00:21:52,978 --> 00:21:54,520
I'm in the wrong business.

507
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:57,231
You know, that's not too far off
how much you owe us.

508
00:21:57,315 --> 00:22:00,485
Really?
'Cause I-I-I had it lower.

509
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:02,362
You had it wrong.

510
00:22:02,446 --> 00:22:03,696
(scoffs) Come on.

511
00:22:03,780 --> 00:22:05,907
You know me,
I'm always good for it.

512
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:07,283
Are you?

513
00:22:07,367 --> 00:22:08,660
'Cause I seem to recall

514
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:10,745
having to push
your Maybach off a cliff.

515
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:12,163
You didn't push shit.

516
00:22:12,247 --> 00:22:13,748
Ray pushed it.

517
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:15,416
It was an S-Class.

518
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:16,793
Who cares? I swear,

519
00:22:16,877 --> 00:22:18,169
you will get your money.

520
00:22:18,253 --> 00:22:20,588
I am, I am this close
to being a judge

521
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:22,090
on <i>Japan's Got Talent.</i>

522
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,217
Oh, terrific.
What kind of watch is that?

523
00:22:24,301 --> 00:22:26,219
This? Oh, this-this is...

524
00:22:26,303 --> 00:22:28,096
a cheap knockoff.
Garbage.

525
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,348
- Let me see it.
- (scoffs) Danny, come on.

526
00:22:30,432 --> 00:22:31,808
- It's-it's junk.
- Ray?

527
00:22:31,892 --> 00:22:33,518
All right, whoa, whoa, whoa.

528
00:22:33,602 --> 00:22:35,478
Slow down. Take it easy.

529
00:22:35,562 --> 00:22:38,523
Look at me, visually deterring.

530
00:22:40,859 --> 00:22:41,818
Richard "Milly"?

531
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:43,820
Ah, it's actually Richard Mille.

532
00:22:43,904 --> 00:22:46,781
Richard Mille.

533
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:48,992
That's a douche way to say it.

534
00:22:49,076 --> 00:22:50,451
Google this, please.

535
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:51,953
Wi-Fi password?

536
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:54,122
- "Serenity."
- Of course it is.

537
00:22:54,206 --> 00:22:57,584
It's, uh, M-I-L-L-E.

538
00:22:59,753 --> 00:23:02,130
You talk to that Jon Cryer much?

539
00:23:02,214 --> 00:23:03,965
Not for a long time, no.

540
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:05,509
He was a hoot.

541
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:08,469
He's my favorite.

542
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:11,139
It was really more
an ensemble show.

543
00:23:11,223 --> 00:23:12,890
RAY:
Son of a bitch.

544
00:23:12,974 --> 00:23:13,975
What?

545
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:17,145
That thing is 150 grand, used.

546
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:19,772
Charlie, I thought
we were friends.

547
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:22,316
We are friends,
but I only owe you 75.

548
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:25,069
- Charlie, Charlie, Charlie...
- Okay, okay, hold on, hold on.

549
00:23:25,153 --> 00:23:28,031
What if I make this right
with some baseball memorabilia?

550
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:29,991
Guys, guys,

551
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:33,703
I've got Babe Ruth's
autopsy report.

552
00:23:33,787 --> 00:23:35,455
- Stop.
- Okay.

553
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:37,582
Okay, uh, uh, how about the hat

554
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:40,502
Barry Bonds wore when he had
a regular-sized head?

555
00:23:42,129 --> 00:23:43,337
Are you done?

556
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:45,298
Yeah.

557
00:23:45,382 --> 00:23:47,341
Listen.

558
00:23:47,425 --> 00:23:49,427
I like you.

559
00:23:49,511 --> 00:23:50,845
I really do.

560
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:53,264
And I admire how you turned
your life around.

561
00:23:53,348 --> 00:23:55,933
Well, thank you, thank you.
I have been working very hard,

562
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:57,643
you know.
I-It's all about the journey.

563
00:23:57,727 --> 00:24:00,147
Whoa, whoa, whoa, enough.

564
00:24:01,815 --> 00:24:03,232
I'm gonna tell you something

565
00:24:03,316 --> 00:24:05,443
I never told a client ever.

566
00:24:06,486 --> 00:24:07,862
I'm listening.

567
00:24:07,946 --> 00:24:10,239
You shouldn't bet on sports.

568
00:24:10,323 --> 00:24:12,241
You shouldn't bet on anything.

569
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:16,370
I mean, if someone's
giving you odds that Wednesday

570
00:24:16,454 --> 00:24:19,874
follows Tuesday, you say,
"Nah, I'm good."

571
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:23,711
But, Danny, it's all I got left.

572
00:24:23,795 --> 00:24:27,757
I understand, but nevertheless,
for a guy like you,

573
00:24:27,841 --> 00:24:29,884
<i>no bueno.</i>

574
00:24:29,968 --> 00:24:32,428
Okay. I hear you.

575
00:24:32,512 --> 00:24:34,847
I appreciate
your concern, and...

576
00:24:34,931 --> 00:24:36,099
I'm gonna take it to heart.

577
00:24:36,183 --> 00:24:38,142
Good.

578
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:39,936
Let's go.

579
00:24:47,694 --> 00:24:49,904
Hey. What was that all about?

580
00:24:49,988 --> 00:24:51,948
I need a new bookie.

581
00:24:55,202 --> 00:24:57,996
(laughter)

582
00:24:59,831 --> 00:25:01,082
What am I missing?

583
00:25:01,166 --> 00:25:03,835
Thing tells time,
whoop-dee-fucking-doo.

584
00:25:03,919 --> 00:25:05,670
If you don't like it,
let me wear it.

585
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:06,921
No.

586
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:08,631
(laughs) Hey, buddy.

587
00:25:08,715 --> 00:25:10,925
We need another pitcher
of the margaritas.

588
00:25:11,009 --> 00:25:12,343
With Don Julio?

589
00:25:12,427 --> 00:25:14,220
We'll take the cheap shit
on the second pass.

590
00:25:14,304 --> 00:25:15,639
- (laughter)
- You got it.

591
00:25:17,098 --> 00:25:18,474
DANNY:
So,

592
00:25:18,558 --> 00:25:19,934
here's what I don't understand.

593
00:25:20,018 --> 00:25:21,561
Pot's off the table,

594
00:25:21,645 --> 00:25:25,148
why don't you switch to selling
other drugs, you know?

595
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:28,067
Like crystal meth.
Kids still like that, right?

596
00:25:28,151 --> 00:25:29,777
(laughs)

597
00:25:29,861 --> 00:25:31,320
You seen what crystal meth
does to people's teeth?

598
00:25:31,404 --> 00:25:32,822
I got a brother who's a dentist.

599
00:25:32,906 --> 00:25:35,116
He showed me pictures.
Can't be a part of that.

600
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,284
DANNY:
Oh.

601
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,119
RAY:
That's... that's noble.

602
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:40,413
I don't know about noble, but
at least I can sleep at night.

603
00:25:40,497 --> 00:25:42,498
After I smoke a bowl,
rub one out.

604
00:25:42,582 --> 00:25:44,960
(laughter)

605
00:25:46,753 --> 00:25:49,255
Oh, I got to do a toast.

606
00:25:49,339 --> 00:25:50,923
To a shitty day

607
00:25:51,007 --> 00:25:53,134
that turned into
a really great day.

608
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:55,553
- Hear, hear. Ah.
<i>- Salud. Salud.</i>

609
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:57,180
DANNY: You mind if I sit
in the front seat?

610
00:25:57,264 --> 00:25:58,598
Be my guest.

611
00:25:58,682 --> 00:26:00,016
Not that I didn't enjoy
our inadvertent

612
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:01,601
dry hump in the back.

613
00:26:01,685 --> 00:26:02,977
RAY (laughs): Hey,
just get your ass in the car.

614
00:26:03,061 --> 00:26:04,187
Give me the watch.

615
00:26:05,313 --> 00:26:06,856
Oh, fuck.

616
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,482
Come on, give me
the fucking watch.

617
00:26:08,566 --> 00:26:10,193
And if I don't,
are you really gonna shoot me?

618
00:26:10,277 --> 00:26:11,903
RAY: It's not worth it, Danny.
Just give him the watch.

619
00:26:11,987 --> 00:26:13,404
But what about our bad day
turning into a good day?

620
00:26:13,488 --> 00:26:15,281
Don't make me
fucking kill you, man.

621
00:26:15,365 --> 00:26:16,365
Shit.

622
00:26:16,449 --> 00:26:18,326
- (sighs)
- What're you doing, Ray?

623
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,368
Yeah, what're you doing?

624
00:26:19,452 --> 00:26:20,661
Protecting the quarterback.

625
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:21,913
- What?
- Throw the ball, Danny.

626
00:26:21,997 --> 00:26:24,832
- What?
- Throw the ball.

627
00:26:24,916 --> 00:26:26,084
DANNY:
Oh.

628
00:26:30,672 --> 00:26:32,632
Anything?

629
00:26:32,716 --> 00:26:34,675
You hit him once.

630
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:35,968
Oh, Jesus.

631
00:26:36,052 --> 00:26:37,345
We got to get out of here.

632
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:42,434
(tires screeching)

633
00:26:57,282 --> 00:26:58,366
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

634
00:27:06,291 --> 00:27:07,834
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

635
00:27:20,597 --> 00:27:22,807
<i>♪ I love Jimmy Luxury ♪</i>

636
00:27:23,683 --> 00:27:25,601
- <i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Hey! Hey! ♪</i>

637
00:27:25,685 --> 00:27:27,561
<i>♪ La-la-la ♪</i>

638
00:27:27,645 --> 00:27:34,402
<i>♪ I'll see you tomorrow
in Havana. ♪</i>

